{
  "texts": [
    "After the geographical analysis, it stands out that 64.28% of the articles evaluated come from the Asian continent, while 14.28% originate from Europe.",
    "Furthermore, it is observed that 7.14% corresponds to both the oceanic and African continents.",
    "In contrast, only 3.57% of the articles come from North America as well as South America.",
    "These findings reveal an evident publication bias, reflected in the lack of uniformity in the distribution of publications across the various continents analyzed.",
    "Regarding the methods and statistical tests used, it is observed that 17.85% of the studies used the Structural Equations Model, followed by t-student (10.71%) and ANOVA (7.14%)."
  ]
}